My royal yacht, the Rizania, smoothly cleaved through the waters of the Zpana river delta.

Ewald Alphonso (R): What a great idea this boat tour w...
en


"What a great idea this boat tour was. It would have been a pity to spend our entire visit trapped in a stuffy old palace."

LineNo: 10250088,

Narrator: I stood on the deck next to Ewald A...
en


I stood on the deck next to Ewald Alphonso, President of Sordland.

LineNo: 10250190,

Narrator: The ship's horn let out a blast as...
en


The ship's horn let out a blast as we passed beneath the bridge.

LineNo: 10250300,

Player_Romus_Italic: I directed the Sordish president's...
en


I directed the Sordish president's attention to the glass skyscrapers of the New Town, where Rizia's banks and major corporations were headquartered.

LineNo: 10250306,

Player_Romus_Italic: I directed the Sordish president's...
Menu Text en


Show Alphonso the New Town.

LineNo: 10250408,

Player_Romus_Italic: I led the Sordish president to the...
en


I led the Sordish president to the southern side of the deck for a better view of the Old Town. The late afternoon sun perfectly illuminated the spire of the Zilba Archsanctuary.

LineNo: 10250414,

Player_Romus_Italic: I led the Sordish president to the...
Menu Text en


Show Alphonso the Old Town.

LineNo: 10250516,

Ewald Alphonso (R): See, this is what I like about you...
en


"See, this is what I like about your country. You're not afraid of the future."

LineNo: 10250642,

Ewald Alphonso (R): Terrific, the way you've preserved...
en


"Terrific, the way you've preserved these historic buildings. But sometimes the past can be a trap."

Player_Romus: Trust me, I know. I've got hundred...
en


"Trust me, I know. I've got hundreds of years of history weighing on me every day."

LineNo: 10250862,

Player_Romus: If my grandmother hadn't made thos...
en


"If my grandmother hadn't made those trade deals between Rizia and Sordland, our countries would still be strangers."

LineNo: 10250964,

Player_Romus: I'm happy your country finally has...
en


"I'm happy your country finally has a president who understands that."

LineNo: 10251066,

Player_Romus: I'm not one to look backwards. Nei...
en


"I'm not one to look backwards. Neither are you, I hear."

LineNo: 10251168,

Player_Romus: Don't let the razzle-dazzle fool y...
en


"Don't let the razzle-dazzle fool you. Rizia is as stuck in the past as it ever was."

LineNo: 10251270,

Player_Romus: Those skyscrapers are an eyesore.
en


"Those skyscrapers are an eyesore."

LineNo: 10251372,

Narrator: Pabel smoothly appeared from behind...
en


Pabel smoothly appeared from behind us with three glasses. Gus handed him the bottle.

LineNo: 10251474,

Narrator: We raised our glasses.
en


We raised our glasses.

LineNo: 10251600,

Player_Romus_Italic: I took a sip without bothering to t...
en


I took a sip without bothering to toast. The two others gave me a puzzled look, then shrugged.

LineNo: 10251606,

Player_Romus_Italic: I took a sip without bothering to t...
Menu Text en


Drink without a toast.

LineNo: 10251708,

Ewald Alphonso (R): To hell with tradition, right?
en


"To hell with tradition, right?"

LineNo: 10251810,

Player_Romus: A Morgna wes core!
en


"A Morgna wes core!"

LineNo: 10251918,

Narrator: The two Sordish men smiled politely...
en


The two Sordish men smiled politely.

LineNo: 10252020,

Player_Romus: To new beginnings.
en


"To new beginnings."

LineNo: 10252128,

Ewald Alphonso (R): And new prosperity.
en


"And new prosperity."

LineNo: 10252230,

Player_Romus: To our ancestors.
en


"To our ancestors."

LineNo: 10252338,

Gus Manger (R): May they rest in peace.
en


"May they rest in peace."

LineNo: 10252440,

Ewald Alphonso (R): Ah, yes. The free trade of Rizian...
en


"Ah, yes. The free trade of Rizian wine for Sordish whiskey. As good a way as any to get our relations flowing again, if you'll pardon the pun."

LineNo: 10252558,

Player_Romus: That can't be the only reason you'...
en


"That can't be the only reason you've traveled all this way."

LineNo: 10252660,

Player_Romus: Sordish whiskey? I'd have to taste...
en


"Sordish whiskey? I'd have to taste it first."

LineNo: 10252762,

Ewald Alphonso (R): I was saving this until after dinn...
en


"I was saving this until after dinner, but here you go."

LineNo: 10252864,

Narrator: He opened his attache and pulled ou...
en


He opened his attache and pulled out a bottle of Erlory Maroon 30-Year-Old.

LineNo: 10252966,

Ewald Alphonso (R): I'll do the toast this time. How d...
en


"I'll do the toast this time. How do you people say it? A proso!"

Narrator: We drank. The flavour rushed over m...
en


We drank. The flavour rushed over my tongue -- wood smoke and forest moss tapering off to a sweet, silky smooth finish.

LineNo: 10253170,

Player_Romus: It's heavenly.
en


"It's heavenly."

LineNo: 10253272,

Player_Romus: Disgusting. Why would anyone want...
en


"Disgusting. Why would anyone want a drink that tastes like trees?"

LineNo: 10253374,

Player_Romus: It's great, but I'd better not hav...
en


"It's great, but I'd better not have any more."

LineNo: 10253476,

Gus Manger (R): And they say royals have sophistic...
en


"And they say royals have sophisticated palates. Your countrymen will go crazy for this."

LineNo: 10253578,

Gus Manger (R): Like tasting the very soul of Erlo...
en


"Like tasting the very soul of Erlory itself."

LineNo: 10253680,

Gus Manger (R): That's liquid gold you're leaving...
en


"That's liquid gold you're leaving in your glass."

LineNo: 10253782,

Ewald Alphonso (R): So, is it a trade, Your Majesty?
en


"So, is it a trade, Your Majesty?"

LineNo: 10253908,

Player_Romus: Definitely. Expect to see all our...
en


"Definitely. Expect to see all our bars serving Sordish whiskey by next year."

LineNo: 10253914,

Player_Romus: Definitely. Expect to see all our...
Menu Text en


"Definitely. Expect to see all our bars serving Sordish whiskey by next year." [Trade Deal]

LineNo: 10254016,

Player_Romus: No. Our wine is so superior to you...
en


"No. Our wine is so superior to your whiskey that it wouldn't be fair to us."

LineNo: 10254118,

Ewald Alphonso (R): Excellent, Your Majesty. Another r...
en


"Excellent, Your Majesty. Another reason for me to return to this gem of a country."

LineNo: 10254220,

Ewald Alphonso (R): But the opportunity they represent...
en


"But the opportunity they represent? Beautiful."

LineNo: 10254322,

Ewald Alphonso (R): You and I are meeting, aren't we?...
en


"You and I are meeting, aren't we? That's already progress."

LineNo: 10254424,

Ewald Alphonso (R): I owe a lot to Colonel Soll. But i...
en


"I owe a lot to Colonel Soll. But it's high time Sordland moved on."

LineNo: 10254526,

Player_Romus: My grandmother was definitely thin...
en


"My grandmother was definitely thinking ahead when she made those trade deals with Sordland years ago."

LineNo: 10254628,

Ewald Alphonso (R): Lyza the Great. It's not easy, liv...
en


"Lyza the Great. It's not easy, living in the shadows of our predecessors."

LineNo: 10254730,

Ewald Alphonso (R): But if my forward-thinking develop...
en


"But if my forward-thinking development minister hadn't reconnected us, we'd still be estranged."

LineNo: 10254832,

Ewald Alphonso (R): Light as a feather compared to the...
en


"Light as a feather compared to the legacy of one Colonel Soll."

LineNo: 10254934,

Narrator: Gus Manger emerged from the ship's...
en


Gus Manger emerged from the ship's cabin, clutching a bottle and grinning triumphantly.

LineNo: 10255036,

Gus Manger (R): Ewald! They have it!
en


"Ewald! They have it!"

LineNo: 10255138,

Gus Manger (R): I tried Cantuavo exactly once, fro...
en


"I tried Cantuavo exactly once, from a Rizian chef in Holsord who smuggled it over in his steamer trunk. Haven't stopped thinking about it ever since."

LineNo: 10255240,

Narrator: He turned to me apologetically.
en


He turned to me apologetically.

LineNo: 10255342,

Gus Manger (R): Our mutual friend Russello mention...
en


"Our mutual friend Russello mentioned your yacht had an excellent wine cellar, and, well, I couldn't help myself."

LineNo: 10255468,

Player_Romus: Mr. Montoro is not my friend. And...
en


"Mr. Montoro is not my friend. And I'd appreciate it if you didn't go rooting around in my ship's quarters."

LineNo: 10255570,

Player_Romus: If you're that impressed by a Cant...
en


"If you're that impressed by a Cantuavo, I hate to think of the swill they must be serving in Sordland."

LineNo: 10255672,

Player_Romus: A man of exquisite taste. I like y...
en


"A man of exquisite taste. I like you already."

LineNo: 10255774,

Narrator: Gus laughed delightedly.
en


Gus laughed delightedly.

LineNo: 10255876,

Gus Manger (R): You hear that, Ewald! Swill! Giral...
en


"You hear that, Ewald! Swill! Giralt of Ribery must be spinning in his grave. Butler!"

LineNo: 10255978,

Player_Romus: Rusty has certainly sampled enough...
en


"Rusty has certainly sampled enough wine to know what he's talking about."

LineNo: 10256080,

Gus Manger (R): Forgive me, Your Majesty. But we c...
en


"Forgive me, Your Majesty. But we can't let this beautiful bottle go to waste now that it's been exposed to sunlight, can we? Butler!"

LineNo: 10256182,

Gus Manger (R): I wouldn't mind gaining some first...
en


"I wouldn't mind gaining some firsthand knowledge myself. Butler!"

LineNo: 10256284,

Gus Manger (R): A toast to exquisite taste, then....
en


"A toast to exquisite taste, then. Butler!"

LineNo: 10256386,

Pabel Adria: Excellent choice, Mr. Manger. Plea...
en


"Excellent choice, Mr. Manger. Please allow me."

LineNo: 10256488,

Narrator: He turned his back as he filled our...
en


He turned his back as he filled our glasses, secretly pouring a nonalcoholic wine substitute into mine. We were used to this routine by now.

LineNo: 10256868,

Narrator: He filled the glasses and handed on...
en


He filled the glasses and handed one to each of us.

LineNo: 10256970,

Pabel Adria: This should taste of cherry and bl...
en


"This should taste of cherry and black pepper, with a faint hint of leather."

LineNo: 10257072,

Ewald Alphonso (R): And stay buried.
en


"And stay buried."

LineNo: 10257174,

Gus Manger (R): And new friends.
en


"And new friends."

Ewald Alphonso (R): We don't usually toast with that p...
en


"We don't usually toast with that phrase. But nice pronunciation."

LineNo: 10257378,

Gus Manger (R): Yes, well done. Vectern sis da.
en


"Yes, well done. Vectern sis da."

LineNo: 10257480,

Gus Manger (R): Right!
en


"Right!"

LineNo: 10257582,

Narrator: We drank. Gus sighed with pure plea...
en


We drank. Gus sighed with pure pleasure. Alphonso's expression bordered on disbelief.

LineNo: 10257684,

Ewald Alphonso (R): All apologies to Giralt of Ribery,...
en


"All apologies to Giralt of Ribery, but this is in fact the best wine I've ever tasted."

LineNo: 10257786,

Gus Manger (R): I told you! I know certain Sordish...
en


"I told you! I know certain Sordish movers and shakers who'd kill to have access to a beverage of this caliber."

LineNo: 10257888,

Gus Manger (R): Which brings me to that deal I sug...
en


"Which brings me to that deal I suggested..."

LineNo: 10257990,

Player_Romus: Rizians do not drink whiskey, Mr....
en


"Rizians do not drink whiskey, Mr. President."

LineNo: 10258092,

Gus Manger (R): Our turn to be the connoisseurs, Y...
en


"Our turn to be the connoisseurs, Your Majesty. Butler! Three tumblers, no ice."

LineNo: 10258194,

Narrator: Pabel approached with three glasses...
en


Pabel approached with three glasses.

LineNo: 10258590,

Player_Romus: Just a small sip for me. To make s...
en


"Just a small sip for me. To make sure my people aren't getting an inferior product."

LineNo: 10258692,

Player_Romus: Actually, I'll take your word for...
en


"Actually, I'll take your word for it. The wine's already gone to my head."

Player_Romus: If I didn't know any better, I'd s...
en


"If I didn't know any better, I'd say you two were trying to get me drunk."

LineNo: 10258896,

Ewald Alphonso (R): I really must insist.
en


"I really must insist."

LineNo: 10258998,

Ewald Alphonso (R): One does not get merely 'drunk' on...
en


"One does not get merely 'drunk' on Erlory Maroon 30-Year-Old. One floats."

LineNo: 10259100,

Player_Romus: I hope this is as good as you say.
en


"I hope this is as good as you say."

LineNo: 10259202,

Ewald Alphonso (R): That's because they've never tried...
en


"That's because they've never tried this."

LineNo: 10259304,

Gus Manger (R): Call it an aperitif.
en


"Call it an aperitif."

LineNo: 10259406,

Narrator: Alphonso opened his attache and pul...
en


Alphonso opened his attache and pulled out a bottle of Erlory Maroon 30-Year-Old.

LineNo: 10259508,

Gus Manger (R): It's even better.
en


"It's even better."

LineNo: 10259610,

Narrator: The yacht lingered at the mouth of...
en


The yacht lingered at the mouth of the Zpana delta as the sun lowered in the sky, turning the water from turquoise to gold.

LineNo: 10259712,

Narrator: A series of looks passed between Gu...
en


A series of looks passed between Gus and Alphonso. They turned back to me.

LineNo: 10259910,

Player_Romus: Yes, sure. Now can we get to the r...
en


"Yes, sure. Now can we get to the real reason why you're here?"

LineNo: 10259916,

Player_Romus: Yes, sure. Now can we get to the r...
Menu Text en


"Yes, sure. Now can we get to the real reason why you're here?" [Trade Deal]

Player_Romus: No, sorry. I'd rather not bring mo...
en


"No, sorry. I'd rather not bring more hard liquor into this country."

LineNo: 10260120,

Gus Manger (R): A shame, Your Majesty. But I do ha...
en


"A shame, Your Majesty. But I do have one more proposal for you."

Ewald Alphonso (R): Excellent, Your Majesty. And yes,...
en


"Excellent, Your Majesty. And yes, there is one more proposal we wanted to discuss."

Ewald Alphonso (R): As much as Sordland's most valued...
en


"As much as Sordland's most valued citizens would appreciate your wine, we believe there's something else they'd find even more stunning."

Narrator: He gestured at his surroundings, th...
en


He gestured at his surroundings, then down at the short-sleeved shirt he was wearing.

LineNo: 10260624,

Gus Manger (R): Have you thought about Rizia's unt...
en


"Have you thought about Rizia's untapped tourism potential, Your Majesty?"

Player_Romus: I'm afraid our conflicts with our...
en


"I'm afraid our conflicts with our neighbors would scare off visitors."

Player_Romus: Yes, many times. Our beaches put L...
en


"Yes, many times. Our beaches put Lespia's to shame, after all."

Player_Romus: We only want the right kind of tou...
en


"We only want the right kind of tourists, Mr. Manger. No riff-raff."

LineNo: 10261056,

Player_Romus: I'm listening...
en


"I'm listening..."

en


"I took the liberty of hiring a designer to draw this up."

LineNo: 10261260,

Gus Manger (R): None indeed.
en


"None indeed."

LineNo: 10261362,

Gus Manger (R): Still, Your Majesty?
en


"Still, Your Majesty?"

LineNo: 10261464,

Gus Manger (R): They're true diamonds in the rough.
en


"They're true diamonds in the rough."

LineNo: 10261566,

Narrator: He reached inside his jacket pocket...
en


He reached inside his jacket pocket and pulled out a sheet of paper with a sketch on it.

LineNo: 10261668,

Narrator: I recognized the beach it depicted....
en


I recognized the beach it depicted. It was a picturesque stretch of sand in Monqiz, not far from the palace where I'd grown up.

LineNo: 10261770,

Narrator: Right on the coastline, the designe...
en


Right on the coastline, the designer had placed a sprawling complex with a swimming pool and tennis courts. On it was a sign: "Koronti Resort Valenqiris".

LineNo: 10261896,

Player_Romus: House Toras would never stand for...
en


"House Toras would never stand for this."

LineNo: 10261998,

Player_Romus: No. I'm not bringing Sordish new m...
en


"No. I'm not bringing Sordish new money to Rizia."

LineNo: 10262100,

Gus Manger (R): New money, old money -- it's all m...
en


"New money, old money -- it's all money. And the investors behind this proposal are itching to spend theirs here."

LineNo: 10262202,

Player_Romus: It's missing a private pier.
en


"It's missing a private pier."

LineNo: 10262304,

Player_Romus: Would that be the senior or the ju...
en


"Would that be the senior or the junior Koronti?"

LineNo: 10262406,

Gus Manger (R): It's only a rough sketch, Your Maj...
en


"It's only a rough sketch, Your Majesty. But yes, a private pier would go without saying."

LineNo: 10262508,

Gus Manger (R): You are the head of House Toras, a...
en


"You are the head of House Toras, are you not?"

LineNo: 10262610,

Gus Manger (R): You've done your research, I see....
en


"You've done your research, I see. This is Marcel's initiative. Along with certain other members of the Lotherberg Group."

LineNo: 10262712,

Narrator: Alphonso swirled the last drops of...
en


Alphonso swirled the last drops of whiskey around in his glass.

LineNo: 10262814,

Ewald Alphonso (R): I'm aware of how your nobles see S...
en


"I'm aware of how your nobles see Sordish oligarchs. I'm also aware that their world-renowned riches have diminished with each successive generation."

LineNo: 10262916,

Ewald Alphonso (R): Change is not merely inevitable, Y...
en


"Change is not merely inevitable, Your Majesty -- it's the only way to preserve the lifestyle to which you're all so accustomed. Your grandmother understood that."

LineNo: 10263042,

Player_Romus: Lyza wouldn't have wanted a bunch...
en


"Lyza wouldn't have wanted a bunch of fat, sunburned vulgarians blocking her ocean views. No offense."

LineNo: 10263144,

Player_Romus: We don't need Sordland's help to s...
en


"We don't need Sordland's help to stay wealthy."

LineNo: 10263246,

Player_Romus: I am the king. The nobles would ha...
en


"I am the king. The nobles would have no choice but to acquiesce."

LineNo: 10263348,

Player_Romus: Well said, Mr. President. My relat...
en


"Well said, Mr. President. My relatives could use a good shock to the system."

LineNo: 10263546,

Gus Manger (R): So that's a yes on the proposal?
en


"So that's a yes on the proposal?"

LineNo: 10263672,

Ewald Alphonso (R): Our partners are considering signi...
en


"Our partners are considering significant investment along the Valenqiris coast. If all went well, the Koronti resort would only be the first step."

LineNo: 10263774,

Narrator: Gus drew his breath in through his...
en


Gus drew his breath in through his teeth.

LineNo: 10263876,

Player_Romus: It is indeed. I hope I'm invited t...
en


"It is indeed. I hope I'm invited to the grand opening."

LineNo: 10263882,

Player_Romus: It is indeed. I hope I'm invited t...
Menu Text en


"It is indeed. I hope I'm invited to the grand opening." [Resort Deal]

Gus Manger (R): You too, eh? We'll assume that's a...
en


"You too, eh? We'll assume that's a no on the proposal, then."

LineNo: 10264110,

Ewald Alphonso (R): We know you've got Queen Beatrice...
en


"We know you've got Queen Beatrice providing her protection. We just wanted to offer you some extra insurance."

LineNo: 10264212,

Gus Manger (R): But we'll assume that's a no on th...
en


"But we'll assume that's a no on the proposal, then?"

LineNo: 10264338,

Player_Romus: Well... I don't like it, but I'd b...
en


"Well... I don't like it, but I'd be a fool to turn down your oligarchs' investment. The answer is yes."

LineNo: 10264344,

Player_Romus: Well... I don't like it, but I'd b...
Menu Text en


"Well... I don't like it, but I'd be a fool to turn down your oligarchs' investment. The answer is yes." [Resort Deal]

LineNo: 10264446,

Player_Romus: You're already getting our wine. T...
en


"You're already getting our wine. That's enough wheeling and dealing for one day."

LineNo: 10264826,

Player_Romus: No, indeed. Come back when you hav...
en


"No, indeed. Come back when you have better ideas."

LineNo: 10264928,

Narrator: Gus laughed.
en


Gus laughed.

LineNo: 10265030,

Gus Manger (R): The King will get a free stay in t...
en


"The King will get a free stay in the largest suite. Anytime he likes."

LineNo: 10265132,

Player_Romus: Yes. As long as the final design i...
en


"Yes. As long as the final design is less gaudy."

LineNo: 10265138,

Player_Romus: Yes. As long as the final design i...
Menu Text en


"Yes. As long as the final design is less gaudy." [Resort Deal]

LineNo: 10265240,

Ewald Alphonso (R): I'll pass that on to our partners.
en


"I'll pass that on to our partners."

LineNo: 10265342,

Player_Romus: No. I do want to open Rizia up to...
en


"No. I do want to open Rizia up to the world, but I'd rather explore other avenues."

LineNo: 10265444,

Ewald Alphonso (R): I see.
en


"I see."

LineNo: 10265546,

Player_Romus: Your assumption is correct. Sorry...
en


"Your assumption is correct. Sorry to waste your time."

LineNo: 10265648,

Narrator: He shrugged.
en


He shrugged.

LineNo: 10265750,

Gus Manger (R): Fair enough.
en


"Fair enough."

LineNo: 10265852,

Narrator: They glanced at each other in surpr...
en


They glanced at each other in surprise.

LineNo: 10265954,

Ewald Alphonso (R): Well. I'm glad we have an understa...
en


"Well. I'm glad we have an understanding!"

LineNo: 10266334,

Narrator: Alphonso shrugged.
en


Alphonso shrugged.

Ewald Alphonso (R): One trade deal is already more tha...
en


"One trade deal is already more than our predecessors managed in 30 years."

LineNo: 10266538,

Ewald Alphonso (R): So the door between our countries...
en


"So the door between our countries will remain closed. For now, at least."

LineNo: 10266640,

Narrator: Alphonso rubbed his hands together.
en


Alphonso rubbed his hands together.

LineNo: 10267020,

Ewald Alphonso (R): In less than an hour, we've accomp...
en


"In less than an hour, we've accomplished more for our countries than our predecessors managed in 30 years."

Ewald Alphonso (R): If the wine will not come to Sordl...
en


"If the wine will not come to Sordland, Sordland will come to the wine. I'm satisfied with that."

Gus Manger (R): Rusty led me to believe you were m...
en


"Rusty led me to believe you were more open-minded than your father. A shame."

LineNo: 10267326,

Gus Manger (R): There's only one opportunity that...
en


"There's only one opportunity that matters to me right now. Butler! Another bottle!"

en


"But no wine in Sordland means that we'd better get our fill of Cantuavo while we're here. Butler! Another bottle!"

LineNo: 10267578,

Player_Romus: His name is Pabel Adria. Show some...
en


"His name is Pabel Adria. Show some respect."

LineNo: 10267680,

Gus Manger (R): Yes, that alone calls for a celebr...
en


"Yes, that alone calls for a celebration. Butler! Another bottle!"

LineNo: 10267806,

Gus Manger (R): I'd say that calls for a celebrati...
en


"I'd say that calls for a celebration. Butler! Another bottle!"

LineNo: 10267932,

Player_Romus: He's my butler, not yours. Pabel!
en


"He's my butler, not yours. Pabel!"

LineNo: 10268034,

Player_Romus: You heard the man, Pabel.
en


"You heard the man, Pabel."

LineNo: 10268142,

Narrator: Pabel reappeared, another bottle in...
en


Pabel reappeared, another bottle in his hands. He filled our glasses with a look of annoyance that only I could detect.
